UID:260504P0f2XWlyXUWiIhCnZCzKzw
DESCRIPTION:This 100km trail race will prove that there’s more than just
  corn in Indiana! Situated in Indiana’s beautiful Morgan Monroe State Fo
 rest\, this evening-start event will have plenty to offer throughout the n
 ight with its old growth forests\, natural rock formations\, lakes\, and c
 reeks. Oh\, and did we mention the hills? With about 8\,500 feet of climbi
 ng—yes\, over 8.5k of climbing!—in addition to southern Indiana’s ty
 pical summertime heat and humidity\, this race is tougher than you’d thi
 nk. Comprised of 85% single track\, 11% forest service road\, and 4% paved
  road \\(but with a generous cutoff time of 20 hours\\)\, we assure you th
 at you won’t be disappointed. \n\nFor those less adventurous trail nuts 
 we offer up our “fun run”.  If you aren’t quite up for the full 100
 km we have a 20 mile loop for you to “enjoy”.  This run will start Sa
 turday June  6 at 8:30am. You will have a SUPER generous 6 hours and 30 m
 inutes to complete one loop. This is the  same loop as the 100k folks wit
 h the same unbelievable support at each aid station. \n\nWe invite you to 
 experience true Hoosier hospitality with our fun and friendly trail runnin
 g community.\n\nCome help make this a trail party…WooHoo! \n\n 
