BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Night of Mandolin Music: the Midwest Mandolin Festival
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260710T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260710T190000
UID:260514gXO-jlXb00qT7Ce0m8VrOQ
DESCRIPTION:“**A Night of Mandolin Music: Jim Richter Presents the Midwe
 st Mandolin Festival**” celebrates mandolin music across its spectrum 
 – orchestral\, folk\, jazz\, bluegrass\, rock\, and blues.\n\nBased in B
 loomington\, Indiana since 2011\, the Jim Richter Mandolin Camp for the Re
 st of Us is in its 13th year and has been a center of mandolin instruction
 \, especially in the genres of blues and rock. This concert features camp 
 faculty: Don Julin (Billy Strings\; writer of Mandolins for Dummies)\, Mik
 e Compton (John Hartford\, Nashville Bluegrass Band\, Oh Brother and Cold 
 Mountain soundtracks)\, Laurelyn Dossett (Rhiannon Giddens\; Levon Helm)\,
  Laura Boosinger (The Knackered Ramblers\, George Shuffler\, Josh Goforth)
  and Jim Richter (blues/rock mandolin educator\; Gordon Bonham). Joining a
 s special guests are Phil Richter\, the Banister Bluegrass Band\, the Colu
 mbus Mandolin Orchestra\, and others.\n\nThis **free event** is sponsore
 d by the Jim Richter Mandolin Camp\, WFHB radio\, the Grant Street Inn\, t
 he Mandolin Café (mandolincafe.com) and Kimble Mandolins.\n\nMore about t
 he camp and its faculty can be found at **www.richtermandolincamp.com**.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://buskirkchumley.org/events/a-night-of-mandolin-music-jim-richte
 r-presents-the-midwest-mandolin-festival-july-10-2026/#buy
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
